\subsection{Accessible Information and Resources}
Provide accessible information and resources, such as travel guides, maps, and online platforms, to assist differently-abled travelers in planning and navigating their trips. This can include visual, auditory, and tactile formats to accommodate a variety of needs.

\subsection{Training for Service Providers}
Offer training for service providers, such as tour guides, hotel staff, and transportation operators, on how to accommodate the needs of differently-abled travelers. This can help ensure that all travelers receive the assistance and support they require.

\section{Conclusion}
By implementing these strategies, we can create a more sustainable, culturally respectful, and accessible international travel experience for all. This will not only benefit travelers but also support local economies, preserve cultural heritage, and promote global understanding and cooperation.

\end{document}
