To display files with type-specific icons in a list using ASP.NET Core with Vue.js and Bootstrap 5, you can follow these steps:

1. Create a new ASP.NET Core project with Vue.js integration:

```bash
dotnet new vue -n FileListApp
cd FileListApp
```

2. Install Bootstrap 5:

```bash
npm install bootstrap@next
```

3. Add Bootstrap 5 to your `wwwroot/index.html` file:

```html
<link href="css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />
```

4. Create a Vue component `FileList.vue`:

```html
<template>
  <div class="container mt-3">
    <div class="list-group">
      <a v-for="file in files" :key="file.name" href="#" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <i :class="getIcon(file.extension)"></i> {{ file.name }}
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</template>

<script>
export default {
  data() {
    return {
      files: [
        { name: "example.txt", extension: "txt" },
        { name: "image.png", extension: "png" },
        { name: "document.pdf", extension: "pdf" },
        // Add more files as needed
      ],
    };
  },
  methods: {
    getIcon(extension) {
      switch (extension) {
        case "txt":
        case "doc":
        case "docx":
          return "bi bi-file-earmark-text";
        case "png":
        case "jpg":
        case "jpeg":
          return "bi bi-file-earmark-image";
        case "pdf":
          return "bi bi-file-earmark-pdf";
        default:
          return "bi bi-file-earmark";
      }
    },
  },
};
</script>

<style scoped>
.list-group-item {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
}
.bi {
  margin-right: 10px;
}
</style>
```

5. Register and use the `FileList` component in your main `App.vue`:

```html
<template>
  <FileList />
</template>

<script>
import FileList from "./components/FileList.vue";

export default {
  components: {
    FileList,
  },
};
</script>
```

